DESCRIPTION:THIS AGREEMENT PROVIDES SUPPORT TO THE STATE OF CONNECTICUT TO IMPLEMENT ITS NONPOINT SOURCE MANAGEMENT PROGRAM, TO CLEAN UP WATER BODIES WITH WATER QUALITY IMPAIRMENTS CAUSED BY POLLUTED RUN-OFF FROM NONPOINT SOURCES. THE CONNECTICUT DEPARTMENT OF ENERGY AND ENVIRONMENTAL PROTECTION WILL FUND ITS SUBRECIPIENTS TO IMPLEMENT NONPOINT SOURCE PROJECTS WHICH INCLUDE A VARIETY OF STRUCTURAL AND NON-STRUCTURAL BEST MANAGEMENT PRACTICES (BMPS), WATERSHED PLANNING, MONITORING, TECHNOLOGY DEMONSTRATIONS, AND A VARIETY OF EDUCATION/OUTREACH PROGRAMS.  ACTIVITIES:THE PROPOSED WORK IN THIS AGREEMENT INCLUDES PROJECTS THAT WILL SUPPORT THE PRIORITIES OF THE GENERAL WORKPLAN: POLLUTION REDUCTION, ESPECIALLY IN TARGETED PRIORITY WATERSHEDS, EDUCATION OF AND GREATER INVOLVEMENT IN WATER REDUCTION ACTIVITIES BY THE PUBLIC AND INTERESTED STAKEHOLDERS, AND COORDINATION WITH PARTNER AGENCIES.SUBRECIPIENT:THESE ACTIVITIES WILL BE IMPLEMENTED THROUGH SUBAWARDS, WHICH INCLUDE:  
THE FIVE SOIL AND WATER CONSERVATION DISTRICTS, CLEAN UP PLANS AND WATER POLLUTION CONTROL ACTIVITIES; 
EASTERN CT CONSERVATION DISTRICT, NATCHAUG WATERSHED ADVISORY BOARD AND WATERSHED BASED PLAN REVIEW; 
MILL RIVER WATERSHED ASSOCIATION; MILL RIVER BIOSWALES PROJECT AND COMMUNITY OUTREACH IN HAMDEN, CT; 
CONNECTICUT DEPARTMENT OF ENERGY AND ENVIRONMENTAL PROTECTION; EVALUATION OF THE CONNECTICUT CWA SECTION 319 PROGRAM;
SAVE THE SOUND: BEARDSLEY PARK GREEN INFRASTRUCTURE AND COMMUNITY OUTREACH; AND
TOWN OF SPRAGUE: SEDIMENT MANAGEMENT FOR HARRINGTON APARTMENTS POND DAM REMOVAL.
OUTCOMES:OUTCOMES WILL INCLUDE IMPROVEMENT AND RESTORATION OF WATER QUALITY IN POLLUTED WATERS, AND PROTECTION OF POTENTIALLY THREATED BUT NOT YET IMPAIRED WATERS, COMPLETED RESTORATION PLANS, AND GREATER UNDERSTANDING OF WATER QUALITY ISSUES AND PARTICIPATION IN IMPROVEMENT ACTIVITIES BY THE PUBLIC. STATEWIDE PROJECTS WILL BENEFIT ALL STATE RESIDENTS. AREA-SPECIFIC PROJECTS WILL BENEFIT THE RESIDENTS OF THE TARGET MUNICIPALITY AND WATERSHED, AND THOSE DOWNSTREAM OF THE AREAS WHERE THE PROJECTS ARE COMPLETED. SUBRECIPIENTS AND DELIVERABLES INCLUDE: 
THE FIVE SOIL AND WATER CONSERVATION DISTRICTS, CLEAN UP PLANS AND WATER POLLUTION CONTROL ACTIVITIES; 
EASTERN CT CONSERVATION DISTRICT, NATCHAUG WATERSHED ADVISORY BOARD AND WATERSHED BASED PLAN REVIEW; 
MILL RIVER WATERSHED ASSOCIATION; MILL RIVER BIOSWALES PROJECT AND COMMUNITY OUTREACH IN HAMDEN, CT; 
CONNECTICUT DEPARTMENT OF ENERGY AND ENVIRONMENTAL PROTECTION; EVALUATION OF THE CONNECTICUT CWA SECTION 319 PROGRAM;
SAVE THE SOUND: BEARDSLEY PARK GREEN INFRASTRUCTURE AND COMMUNITY OUTREACH; AND
TOWN OF SPRAGUE: SEDIMENT MANAGEMENT FOR HARRINGTON APARTMENTS POND DAM REMOVAL.

